## Motion System (Sitewide Animation Unification)

### Overview
All site animations use a unified motion system powered by **Motion One** (framework-agnostic WAAPI-based library). This ensures smooth 60fps animations even on slower devices and compatibility with future Astro migration.

### Technology Choice: Motion One
- **Bundle size:** ~2-3KB (vs ~17-27KB for Framer Motion)
- **Performance:** S-Tier compositor thread animations (uninterruptible by main thread blocking)
- **Astro compatibility:** Framework-agnostic, works natively without React hydration
- **Migration path:** Code written for Motion One works in both Gatsby and Astro

### Global Constants (All Animations)

| Setting | Desktop | Mobile |
|---------|---------|--------|
| **Duration** | 800ms (varies by element) | 800ms (varies by element) |
| **Easing** | `cubic-bezier(0.2, 0.8, 0.2, 1)` | Same |
| **Trigger** | `rootMargin: '0px 0px -15% 0px'` | `rootMargin: '0px 0px -10% 0px'` |
| **Behavior** | `once: true` | `once: true` |
| **Threshold** | Default | 0.05 (5%) |
| **Constraint** | - | Disable lateral movement if width > 90% viewport |

### Standardized Timing Table (All Pages)

| Element Type | Delay | Duration | Effect |
|--------------|-------|----------|--------|
| Section Header | 0ms | 800ms | Slide up 30px + Fade |
| Primary Column/Unit | 150ms | 700ms | Slide up 20px + Fade |
| Secondary Unit | +100ms | 700ms | Slide up 20px + Fade |
| Illustrations/Media | 300ms | 1000ms | Pure Fade or Soft Scale (0.98 â†’ 1.0) |

